author: sussman
msg: Bugfix:  'svn co -q' has been segfaulting.
This bug was written, oh, about a year and a half ago.  Apparently
nobody has *ever* tried to pass '-q' to 'svn checkout', until gstein
added that flag to dist.sh in r1172... I think.  Still a mystery,
though.  How was dist.sh working at all for the last few tarballs?
* CHANGES:  increment version number of 0.10.1
* compose_editors.c (svn_delta_wrap_editor):  if before- and after-
editors are both NULL, then just return the original editor.
